1
00:00:08,583 --> 00:00:10,208
[NARRATOR] The conflict between
England and France

2
00:00:10,291 --> 00:00:12,791
continued to escalate
and was set to reach its climax

3
00:00:12,875 --> 00:00:14,708
at the Siege of Orleans.

4
00:00:14,791 --> 00:00:17,333
If the English were to succeed
in conquering the city,

5
00:00:17,416 --> 00:00:18,791
they would surely
be able to topple

6
00:00:18,875 --> 00:00:21,458
the rest of southern France
with relative ease.

7
00:00:21,541 --> 00:00:24,375
On the other hand,
if France were to defend Orleans

8
00:00:24,458 --> 00:00:26,125
from being taken by the English,

9
00:00:26,208 --> 00:00:28,208
they would then be able
to escort Princess Charlotte

10
00:00:28,291 --> 00:00:29,833
to her coronation ceremony.

11
00:00:29,916 --> 00:00:32,916
In service of the cause,
Montmorency was hard at work,

12
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:36,250
attempting to lead a regiment of
about a hundred men to Orleans,

13
00:00:36,333 --> 00:00:37,625
along with provisions.

14
00:00:37,708 --> 00:00:39,666
However, the only bridge
they could use

15
00:00:39,750 --> 00:00:41,791
to cross the Loire
was already occupied

16
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:43,000
by the English army,

17
00:00:43,083 --> 00:00:44,833
and the impregnable
Tourelles complex

18
00:00:44,916 --> 00:00:46,166
sat on the southern shore,

19
00:00:46,250 --> 00:00:48,291
preventing Montmorency
from crossing.

20
00:00:52,791 --> 00:00:55,583
[MONTMORENCY] A frontal assault
will be quite difficult.

21
00:00:55,666 --> 00:00:57,791
-[grunting]
-Hmm.

22
00:00:59,541 --> 00:01:00,958
[MONTMORENCY]
It looks like our only option

23
00:01:01,041 --> 00:01:02,666
is to sneak around
to the eastern side,

24
00:01:02,750 --> 00:01:04,250
where it's not
as heavily guarded,

25
00:01:04,333 --> 00:01:07,000
and transport the provisions
across the Loire on boats.

26
00:01:08,333 --> 00:01:10,041
-Astaroth.
-[ASTAROTH] Hmm?

27
00:01:10,125 --> 00:01:11,875
[MONTMORENCY] Find the
commanding officer in Orleans.

28
00:01:11,958 --> 00:01:14,083
Have him send us troops
to use as a diversion.

29
00:01:14,166 --> 00:01:15,625
[sighs]
Yeah, yeah.

30
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,250
[ASTAROTH sighs]

31
00:01:20,333 --> 00:01:21,708
[ASTAROTH] All this work
almost makes me wish

32
00:01:21,791 --> 00:01:22,666
I couldn't fly.

33
00:01:22,750 --> 00:01:24,000
[SOLDIERS clamoring]

34
00:03:18,375 --> 00:03:20,375
Bring everything to the barn
in back.

35
00:03:20,458 --> 00:03:22,333
And please be careful,
there's no need to rush.

36
00:03:22,416 --> 00:03:23,375
We're almost there!

37
00:03:23,458 --> 00:03:25,416
I believe in every one of you.

38
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:26,666
[BATARD]
Montmorency.

39
00:03:26,750 --> 00:03:28,000
Oh, hello, Batard.

40
00:03:28,083 --> 00:03:29,333
-[JEANNE gasps]
-Long time no see.

41
00:03:29,416 --> 00:03:31,958
Oh, wow! had no idea
the commanding officer

42
00:03:32,041 --> 00:03:33,333
was a princess knight.

43
00:03:33,416 --> 00:03:35,416
Uh, I'm not a girl, I'm male.

44
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:36,916
It's just that
my cousin, Charlotte,

45
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,541
has forced me to dress
in girls' clothing

46
00:03:38,625 --> 00:03:41,333
ever since I was a baby,
so I get why you'd think that.

47
00:03:41,416 --> 00:03:43,791
I don't want a boy cousin.

48
00:03:43,875 --> 00:03:46,291
I want a girl to play with,
someone like me.

49
00:03:46,375 --> 00:03:47,583
Oh. I see.

50
00:03:47,666 --> 00:03:48,916
Well, that explains
why your chest

51
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,125
is even flatter than mine.

52
00:03:50,208 --> 00:03:52,291
[screams]

53
00:03:52,375 --> 00:03:54,458
Girls scare me a little,
so please don't touch.

54
00:03:54,541 --> 00:03:55,875
[MONTMORENCY]
Being bullied by Charlotte

55
00:03:55,958 --> 00:03:57,333
left him with some scars, I see.

56
00:03:57,416 --> 00:03:58,833
[BATARD] I'm not scared
of gentlemen, though.

57
00:03:58,916 --> 00:04:01,125
So feel free to touch me
if you'd like, Montmorency.

58
00:04:01,208 --> 00:04:02,833
[MONTMORENCY]
I think I'll pass.

59
00:04:02,916 --> 00:04:04,916
[JEANNE] If you don't want to,
then why are your cheeks so red?

60
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,958
[MONTMORENCY]
Could we focus, please?

61
00:04:07,041 --> 00:04:09,291
-Ugh. What a bunch of fools.
-[MONTMORENCY] Huh?

62
00:04:09,375 --> 00:04:11,333
I'd heard rumors, but I wasn't
prepared to see you

63
00:04:11,416 --> 00:04:13,041
with an archangel on your hat.

64
00:04:13,125 --> 00:04:14,333
Who's he?

65
00:04:14,416 --> 00:04:15,375
Alencon.

66
00:04:15,458 --> 00:04:17,666
Richemont's younger brother.

67
00:04:20,166 --> 00:04:21,833
My sister is a selfish brat.

68
00:04:21,916 --> 00:04:23,541
Don't say that.

69
00:04:23,625 --> 00:04:25,083
[ALENCON] She is a disgrace
to the tradition of knighthood.

70
00:04:25,166 --> 00:04:26,583
[BATARD]
Uh-uh.

71
00:04:26,666 --> 00:04:28,791
Well, at least we have her.

72
00:04:28,875 --> 00:04:30,791
I have always dreamed
of fighting alongside

73
00:04:30,875 --> 00:04:32,541
an inexperienced shepherdess.

74
00:04:32,625 --> 00:04:34,375
[giggles]
I'm flattered.

75
00:04:34,458 --> 00:04:36,583
[MONTMORENCY] You're not
familiar with sarcasm, are you?

76
00:04:36,666 --> 00:04:37,875
Huh?

77
00:04:37,958 --> 00:04:39,916
It's not too late
to turn this around.

78
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,625
Send the poor thing
back to Domremy.

79
00:04:41,708 --> 00:04:43,083
[JEANNE]
What?

80
00:04:43,166 --> 00:04:44,666
[door opens]

81
00:04:44,750 --> 00:04:46,583
[SOLDIER] They're about to break
through the front line!

82
00:04:46,666 --> 00:04:48,125
[ALENCON]
I'll be right down.

83
00:04:48,208 --> 00:04:50,375
Don't you understand,
Montmorency?

84
00:04:50,458 --> 00:04:52,166
Dressing a poor shepherd girl
in armor

85
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:53,750
and throwing her into battle

86
00:04:53,833 --> 00:04:56,041
violates the very code
of chivalry we knights live by.

87
00:04:57,291 --> 00:05:00,083
[MONTMORENCY] He's even more
insufferable than he used to be.

88
00:05:00,166 --> 00:05:02,125
It's not been easy for him,

89
00:05:02,208 --> 00:05:03,958
living in his sister's shadow
all these years.

90
00:05:05,083 --> 00:05:06,250
[JEANNE sighs]

91
00:05:07,708 --> 00:05:09,083
♪

92
00:05:09,166 --> 00:05:10,666
[neighs]

93
00:05:13,291 --> 00:05:15,833
[ALENCON] You must view this
as an opportunity, Alencon.

94
00:05:15,916 --> 00:05:17,791
If you shift the tide of this
battle on your own,

95
00:05:17,875 --> 00:05:19,750
without your sister
getting in the way,

96
00:05:19,833 --> 00:05:21,083
then no one can ever call you

97
00:05:21,166 --> 00:05:23,000
the useless
little brother again.

98
00:05:23,083 --> 00:05:25,000
♪

99
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,625
[SOLDIERS clamoring]

100
00:05:32,083 --> 00:05:33,250
[ALENCON]
Fear not, men.

101
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:35,416
Justice is on our side!

102
00:05:35,500 --> 00:05:39,000
Therefore, God is
on the side of France as well!

103
00:05:40,833 --> 00:05:42,750
[neighing]

104
00:05:46,708 --> 00:05:47,666
Hyah!

105
00:05:51,541 --> 00:05:52,791
[gasps]

106
00:05:52,875 --> 00:05:54,208
Out of my way!

107
00:05:55,666 --> 00:05:56,625
What?!

108
00:06:00,875 --> 00:06:01,958
[grunts]

109
00:06:03,208 --> 00:06:04,541
[groaning]

110
00:06:06,125 --> 00:06:07,208
[ALENCON]
What on earth was that?

111
00:06:07,291 --> 00:06:09,791
♪

112
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:17,083
[gasping]

113
00:06:17,166 --> 00:06:19,125
[JEANNE]
Why not fight me instead?

114
00:06:19,208 --> 00:06:20,916
I'm a worthy adversary.

115
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,208
[ALENCON] Is this
the same girl from before?

116
00:06:30,291 --> 00:06:31,500
What happened?

117
00:06:31,583 --> 00:06:33,375
She carries herself
like a warrior now.

118
00:06:33,458 --> 00:06:34,750
Who are you, then?

119
00:06:36,416 --> 00:06:37,875
I'm Ulysses Noire.

120
00:06:37,958 --> 00:06:39,458
[JEANNE]
Noire?

121
00:06:39,541 --> 00:06:41,416
You call yourself
the Black Ulysses?

122
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:43,083
Interesting.

123
00:06:43,166 --> 00:06:44,875
Then I shall test your mettle.

124
00:06:44,958 --> 00:06:47,875
Let us see if you deserve
to bear the name Ulysses.

125
00:06:47,958 --> 00:06:50,333
♪

126
00:07:02,458 --> 00:07:04,708
[ALENCON] This is no fight
between mere mortals.

127
00:07:06,291 --> 00:07:08,416
[ULYSSES NOIRE]
I've been dying to watch you.

128
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:10,458
Honestly, the main reason
I came here

129
00:07:10,541 --> 00:07:13,375
is to see you in action
on the battlefield. [laughs]

130
00:07:13,458 --> 00:07:15,125
[JEANNE] You wont be laughing
for much longer!

131
00:07:15,208 --> 00:07:16,708
♪

132
00:07:16,791 --> 00:07:18,333
[grunting]

133
00:07:23,625 --> 00:07:25,500
-[JEANNE chuckles]
-[ULYSSES NOIRE] She's too fast.

134
00:07:25,583 --> 00:07:26,500
[groans]

135
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:29,375
[grunts]

136
00:07:29,458 --> 00:07:31,000
[panting]

137
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:35,000
[grunting]

138
00:07:35,083 --> 00:07:36,500
♪

139
00:07:45,041 --> 00:07:46,333
[scoffs]

140
00:07:46,416 --> 00:07:48,708
I can't believe you actually
dodged my attack.

141
00:07:48,791 --> 00:07:50,166
[chuckles]

142
00:07:50,250 --> 00:07:52,750
-[MONTMORENCY] Jeanne!
-[ULYSSES NOIRE gasps]

143
00:07:52,833 --> 00:07:53,750
Come back!

144
00:07:55,625 --> 00:07:57,291
[MONTMORENCY]
Stop chasing her.

145
00:07:57,375 --> 00:08:00,041
Remember, you can only fight as
Ulysses three minutes at a time.

146
00:08:00,125 --> 00:08:01,166
Ugh!

147
00:08:06,250 --> 00:08:07,541
[MONTMORENCY]
Are you all right?

148
00:08:11,250 --> 00:08:12,166
[sighs]

149
00:08:13,291 --> 00:08:15,166
[yelling]

150
00:08:15,250 --> 00:08:17,000
Fall back at once!

151
00:08:18,791 --> 00:08:21,208
I am just so honored!

152
00:08:21,291 --> 00:08:23,375
To bask in the presence
of a real saint?

153
00:08:23,458 --> 00:08:25,500
I can't believe
I would be so lucky!

154
00:08:25,583 --> 00:08:26,791
I never knew there was a woman

155
00:08:26,875 --> 00:08:28,708
as wonderful as you
in the entire world!

156
00:08:28,791 --> 00:08:31,041
Relax, you can give her
a handshake later.

157
00:08:31,125 --> 00:08:33,291
Oh, no, I'd prefer
not to, thanks.

158
00:08:39,041 --> 00:08:40,541
[groans]

159
00:08:42,833 --> 00:08:43,875
[grunts]

160
00:08:47,916 --> 00:08:51,166
♪

161
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:52,791
[BEDFORD]
Ulysses.

162
00:08:52,875 --> 00:08:55,708
I suppose they're saying
the legends are true, then.

163
00:08:55,791 --> 00:08:57,583
Overwhelming fighting power?

164
00:08:57,666 --> 00:08:58,750
I'll buy that.

165
00:08:58,833 --> 00:09:00,458
But England has always
been known

166
00:09:00,541 --> 00:09:02,708
as a land of monsters, too.

167
00:09:02,791 --> 00:09:05,166
When one studies
our military history,

168
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:06,583
they essentially study
the history

169
00:09:06,666 --> 00:09:08,666
of hunting abominations.

170
00:09:08,750 --> 00:09:11,333
This is nothing we haven't
encountered before.

171
00:09:11,416 --> 00:09:14,333
Isn't that right, Glasdale?

172
00:09:14,416 --> 00:09:15,708
[GLASDALE]
It's gonna cost ya.

173
00:09:15,791 --> 00:09:17,291
[BEDFORD]
Don't worry about that.

174
00:09:17,375 --> 00:09:19,833
Money is no obstacle
to our aims.

175
00:09:19,916 --> 00:09:22,041
Bring her to me dead or alive.

176
00:09:22,125 --> 00:09:25,000
Hunt down that hideous monster.

177
00:09:25,083 --> 00:09:28,458
Forgive me if my saying
"monster" was insensitive.

178
00:09:28,541 --> 00:09:30,000
I meant no offense.

179
00:09:30,083 --> 00:09:32,458
[BEDFORD laughs]

180
00:09:32,541 --> 00:09:33,583
[chuckles]

181
00:09:33,666 --> 00:09:35,333
[GLASDALE]
I hope you can refrain

182
00:09:35,416 --> 00:09:38,250
from taking matters
into your own hands next time.

183
00:09:38,333 --> 00:09:40,416
We work as a team or not at all.

184
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:41,583
[ULYSSES NOIRE]
Yes.

185
00:09:41,666 --> 00:09:43,166
[chuckles]

186
00:09:45,875 --> 00:09:47,375
[cheering]

187
00:09:47,458 --> 00:09:48,625
[MAN 1]
Our beloved saint!

188
00:09:48,708 --> 00:09:50,416
[MAN 2]
The Blessed Maiden of Domremy!

189
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:52,291
[MAN 3] The archangel
is with them as well!

190
00:09:52,375 --> 00:09:55,041
I don't feel right
receiving this praise.

191
00:09:55,125 --> 00:09:56,166
I'm not a real savior,

192
00:09:56,250 --> 00:09:58,166
so the fanfare
makes me feel bad.

193
00:09:58,250 --> 00:09:59,833
[ASTAROTH]
Stop with that nonsense.

194
00:09:59,916 --> 00:10:01,833
You are a real savior
in your own right.

195
00:10:01,916 --> 00:10:03,791
Really?

196
00:10:03,875 --> 00:10:06,041
Well, then, thank you!

197
00:10:06,125 --> 00:10:07,333
Thank you!

198
00:10:07,416 --> 00:10:09,291
Let's beat England as one!

199
00:10:09,375 --> 00:10:11,833
♪

200
00:10:11,916 --> 00:10:14,000
I still can't believe you were
able to get past

201
00:10:14,083 --> 00:10:15,833
an English fortress so easily.

202
00:10:15,916 --> 00:10:19,291
The most important factor in war
is the person in command.

203
00:10:19,375 --> 00:10:21,291
Also, at this time of year,

204
00:10:21,375 --> 00:10:23,041
strong winds blow
in from the Loire

205
00:10:23,125 --> 00:10:25,958
at certain times of day,
and I know when they do.

206
00:10:26,041 --> 00:10:28,583
Light up a fire, and the rest
will take care of itself.

207
00:10:28,666 --> 00:10:30,500
France is our country.

208
00:10:30,583 --> 00:10:32,666
-We've a geographical advantage.
-[gasping]

209
00:10:32,750 --> 00:10:33,875
[laughs]

210
00:10:33,958 --> 00:10:35,833
[BATARD] You're the best,
Montmorency!

211
00:10:35,916 --> 00:10:37,208
[MONTMORENCY]
Please, I mean no offense,

212
00:10:37,291 --> 00:10:38,416
but I don't like boys.

213
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:39,416
[BATARD laughing]

214
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:41,041
[grunts]
Enough!

215
00:10:44,125 --> 00:10:46,083
[MONTMORENCY]
Um, sorry.

216
00:10:53,166 --> 00:10:54,208
[gasps]

217
00:10:54,291 --> 00:10:56,750
♪

218
00:10:58,833 --> 00:10:59,958
[JEANNE moaning]

219
00:11:12,083 --> 00:11:13,083
[exhales]

220
00:11:13,166 --> 00:11:15,208
That's so rejuvenating.

221
00:11:15,291 --> 00:11:17,000
Would it kill you
to ask me for once?

222
00:11:17,083 --> 00:11:19,583
Sorry. I can't help it.

223
00:11:19,666 --> 00:11:23,000
I simply don't feel like myself
unless I've had a little elixir.

224
00:11:23,083 --> 00:11:24,750
♪

225
00:11:32,250 --> 00:11:33,250
[MONTMORENCY groans]

226
00:11:33,333 --> 00:11:35,041
[JEANNE]
I need more, Montmorency.

227
00:11:35,125 --> 00:11:37,125
Just a little, and then I
promise I'll leave you alone.

228
00:11:37,208 --> 00:11:38,916
[MONTMORENCY] Get away!
Now you're just being greedy.

229
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,166
[JEANNE]
No, I need more. Please!

230
00:11:40,250 --> 00:11:41,541
[MONTMORENCY]
You've had plenty.

231
00:11:41,625 --> 00:11:42,750
This is absurd.
Leave me be!

232
00:11:44,791 --> 00:11:46,541
[JEANNE breathing heavily]

233
00:11:57,958 --> 00:12:00,041
Ugh! This is wrong.

234
00:12:00,125 --> 00:12:02,708
Why'd I agree
to let her sleep here?

235
00:12:02,791 --> 00:12:04,208
[ASTAROTH]
Montmorency.

236
00:12:04,291 --> 00:12:05,500
The more Jeanne kisses you,

237
00:12:05,583 --> 00:12:07,500
the faster your feelings
toward her change.

238
00:12:07,583 --> 00:12:08,875
You're starting to see her

239
00:12:08,958 --> 00:12:10,125
as an attractive member
of the opposite sex.

240
00:12:10,208 --> 00:12:11,500
It's not like that.

241
00:12:11,583 --> 00:12:13,458
[ASTAROTH] But you are male,
and she's female.

242
00:12:13,541 --> 00:12:16,083
You cannot deny your
primal instinct to procreate.

243
00:12:16,166 --> 00:12:17,500
Humans are no different
from animals

244
00:12:17,583 --> 00:12:18,958
in that regard, unfortunately.

245
00:12:19,041 --> 00:12:21,541
[MONTMORENCY]
This is absolutely wrong.

246
00:12:21,625 --> 00:12:23,916
I have to come up
with a solution at once.

247
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,541
[MONTMORENCY grunts
in frustration]

248
00:12:25,625 --> 00:12:27,541
There is one solution
that comes to mind.

249
00:12:27,625 --> 00:12:28,916
[MONTMORENCY]
What is it?

250
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,166
[ASTAROTH]
I need the Stone.

251
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:32,208
[MONTMORENCY]
Huh? Okay.

252
00:12:36,333 --> 00:12:39,958
♪

253
00:12:40,041 --> 00:12:41,166
[gasps]

254
00:12:42,208 --> 00:12:43,291
Who is this?

255
00:12:43,375 --> 00:12:45,083
If you manage
to harness the power

256
00:12:45,166 --> 00:12:47,833
of the Philosopher's Stone
to its fullest extent,

257
00:12:47,916 --> 00:12:51,125
this ethereal beauty
will devote herself to you.

258
00:12:51,208 --> 00:12:53,416
I had no idea
the Philosopher's Stone

259
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:55,000
held such secrets.

260
00:12:56,083 --> 00:12:59,083
I assure you,
if you take her into your arms,

261
00:12:59,166 --> 00:13:02,416
you will never again be charmed
by the wiles of human women.

262
00:13:03,375 --> 00:13:04,916
-[MONTMORENCY] I can't do it.
-[ASTAROTH] Hmm?

263
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,333
[MONTMORENCY]
I won't deny

264
00:13:06,416 --> 00:13:08,375
the intoxicating
power of her beauty.

265
00:13:08,458 --> 00:13:11,166
Nevertheless, true love
cannot be built

266
00:13:11,250 --> 00:13:12,375
on physical attraction alone.

267
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:14,625
You have to know
your partner deeply.

268
00:13:15,666 --> 00:13:17,666
[chuckles]
Fooled you, huh?

269
00:13:17,750 --> 00:13:20,375
That's just something I read
once in a silly romance novel.

270
00:13:20,458 --> 00:13:21,666
[ASTAROTH sighs]

271
00:13:25,458 --> 00:13:28,458
Uh...
Where are you going?

272
00:13:30,875 --> 00:13:32,416
[ASTAROTH]
No one has succeeded yet.

273
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:34,791
No wielder of the Stone
has been able to hold her.

274
00:13:34,875 --> 00:13:36,833
I blame heroes
and their lust for glory.

275
00:13:36,916 --> 00:13:39,041
They swarm like moths
to the fires of war,

276
00:13:39,125 --> 00:13:40,958
blinded by their desire
for power.

277
00:13:42,166 --> 00:13:44,916
And, thus, every one of them
chooses to forget her.

278
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:47,208
♪

279
00:13:57,166 --> 00:13:58,708
[MONTMORENCY]
What's going on out there?

280
00:13:58,791 --> 00:14:01,166
The peasants are
attacking the tower.

281
00:14:01,250 --> 00:14:02,458
[MAN 1]
We're tired of the English

282
00:14:02,541 --> 00:14:03,875
doing whatever they please.

283
00:14:03,958 --> 00:14:05,875
We'll stop them
once and for all.

284
00:14:05,958 --> 00:14:08,083
[MAN 2] We have a saint
fighting on our side.

285
00:14:08,166 --> 00:14:09,416
[MAN 3]
If we die in battle,

286
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:11,166
we shall be rewarded
in the kingdom of God!

287
00:14:11,250 --> 00:14:13,625
[MONTMORENCY] They're heading
toward the Tourelles complex?

288
00:14:13,708 --> 00:14:16,333
But all the English troops are
holed up inside the fortress.

289
00:14:16,416 --> 00:14:18,166
They'll all be slaughtered.

290
00:14:18,250 --> 00:14:19,833
We don't have a sound strategy

291
00:14:19,916 --> 00:14:21,916
for defeating
Ulysses Noire, either.

292
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,666
So why didn't you stop them?

293
00:14:23,750 --> 00:14:25,083
[BATARD]
I tried, believe me,

294
00:14:25,166 --> 00:14:26,916
but none of them
would listen to a word I said.

295
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,333
[ALENCON]
This whole thing is your fault.

296
00:14:28,416 --> 00:14:29,458
Excuse me?

297
00:14:31,541 --> 00:14:34,083
If morale is too low,
people refuse to follow orders.

298
00:14:34,166 --> 00:14:35,375
But if they get too worked up,

299
00:14:35,458 --> 00:14:37,708
they become even
harder to control.

300
00:14:37,791 --> 00:14:39,083
You and that saint.

301
00:14:39,166 --> 00:14:41,208
You filled their heads
with fanatic nonsense.

302
00:14:47,208 --> 00:14:49,458
I will take command.
Any objections?

303
00:14:49,541 --> 00:14:50,875
Uh...

304
00:14:50,958 --> 00:14:52,250
[ALENCON] This violates
the code of chivalry,

305
00:14:52,333 --> 00:14:53,916
but as we are desperate,

306
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,958
we must use the mob headed
to Les Tourelles as a diversion

307
00:14:56,041 --> 00:14:58,416
and direct our forces
toward the other fortress.

308
00:14:58,500 --> 00:15:00,041
We'll have to accept
that many will die,

309
00:15:00,125 --> 00:15:01,291
but it won't be in vain.

310
00:15:02,416 --> 00:15:04,625
[MONTMORENCY] That's a logical
course of action.

311
00:15:04,708 --> 00:15:07,166
Richemont trained him to be
a highly effective warrior.

312
00:15:07,250 --> 00:15:09,333
[JEANNE]
Count Alencon, we can't do that.

313
00:15:10,375 --> 00:15:11,916
[MONTMORENCY]
Jeanne.

314
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:14,708
We must fight alongside
those headed towards Tourelles.

315
00:15:14,791 --> 00:15:17,541
We came all this way to save
the citizens of Orleans,

316
00:15:17,625 --> 00:15:19,541
and if we use them
as a diversion,

317
00:15:19,625 --> 00:15:21,416
the journey to this point
will have been for nothing.

318
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:23,166
We simply don't have
the manpower

319
00:15:23,250 --> 00:15:25,125
to stand a chance
against professional soldiers

320
00:15:25,208 --> 00:15:26,916
guarding an impregnable
fortress.

321
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,666
[JEANNE]
I'll fight at Les Tourelles,

322
00:15:28,750 --> 00:15:30,250
even if I have to go alone.

323
00:15:30,333 --> 00:15:31,916
But, Jeanne, if you get
killed there,

324
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:34,500
then Orleans will surely
fall to the English!

325
00:15:34,583 --> 00:15:37,916
And if that happens, the English
soldiers will work themselves

326
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:39,500
into a frenzy of bloodlust,

327
00:15:39,583 --> 00:15:41,083
and they won't care
that I'm a boy.

328
00:15:41,166 --> 00:15:43,541
They'll just take me anyway
and use me as they please!

329
00:15:43,625 --> 00:15:46,166
[crying]
Oh! I want my mother!

330
00:15:46,250 --> 00:15:49,333
War calls for careful strategy
and discipline.

331
00:15:49,416 --> 00:15:51,708
If our emotions take over,
then we are lost.

332
00:15:51,791 --> 00:15:54,416
-We'll fall to them one by one.
-Please help me!

333
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:55,958
You must remain strong.

334
00:15:56,041 --> 00:15:57,458
And, Jeanne...

335
00:15:57,541 --> 00:15:59,083
[grunts]

336
00:15:59,166 --> 00:16:00,666
[ASTAROTH] Jeanne's emotions
are reverberating

337
00:16:00,750 --> 00:16:02,000
against the power of the Stone.

338
00:16:02,083 --> 00:16:03,291
She's on the verge
of losing control.

339
00:16:03,375 --> 00:16:04,750
How can we stop it?

340
00:16:04,833 --> 00:16:06,541
[ASTAROTH]
We can't, I'm afraid.

341
00:16:06,625 --> 00:16:08,083
No one can stop her
at this point,

342
00:16:08,166 --> 00:16:09,541
she's too far gone.

343
00:16:11,125 --> 00:16:13,375
[SOLDIERS yelling]

344
00:16:14,375 --> 00:16:16,416
What a strange turn of events.

345
00:16:19,875 --> 00:16:21,416
-[yelling]
-[grunting]

346
00:16:24,875 --> 00:16:27,583
[grunts, groans]

347
00:16:27,666 --> 00:16:28,666
[ALENCON]
Damn it!

348
00:16:32,166 --> 00:16:35,791
Who would've thought they'd
attack head-on with no strategy?

349
00:16:35,875 --> 00:16:38,625
That movement reeks
of sheer desperation.

350
00:16:38,708 --> 00:16:40,083
Well, no matter.

351
00:16:40,166 --> 00:16:41,625
I am here to do a job

352
00:16:41,708 --> 00:16:43,916
and I'll follow through,
regardless.

353
00:16:46,208 --> 00:16:47,750
[JEANNE]
I'm sorry, Montmorency.

354
00:16:47,833 --> 00:16:49,166
There's no need to be sorry

355
00:16:49,250 --> 00:16:50,666
that you're fighting
for the lives of peasants.

356
00:16:50,750 --> 00:16:51,833
I expect that.

357
00:16:51,916 --> 00:16:53,375
Now, if you'd agreed
with Alencon,

358
00:16:53,458 --> 00:16:55,416
-I'd have been shocked.
-[JEANNE] Hmm.

359
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:57,083
Wait for the right moment,
you got it?

360
00:16:57,166 --> 00:16:58,125
[JEANNE]
Hmm.

361
00:16:58,208 --> 00:17:00,208
[MAN 1]
God save the maiden!

362
00:17:00,291 --> 00:17:02,458
[MAN 2] You are no longer men
but shields for her,

363
00:17:02,541 --> 00:17:04,125
Heroes of Orleans!

364
00:17:04,208 --> 00:17:05,666
[SOLDIER 1] These are not
the French peasants

365
00:17:05,750 --> 00:17:07,208
we're accustomed to fighting.

366
00:17:07,291 --> 00:17:09,541
[SOLDIER 2] The witch of Domremy
turned them into demons!

367
00:17:09,625 --> 00:17:11,666
She's made them immortal!

368
00:17:11,750 --> 00:17:14,583
[ALENCON] Their fear
is giving over to passion.

369
00:17:14,666 --> 00:17:17,541
So far, it's just as
Montmorency predicted.

370
00:17:17,625 --> 00:17:19,250
[gasps]

371
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:21,208
[GLASDALE]
Where's the Ulysses?

372
00:17:22,208 --> 00:17:23,375
Glasdale.

373
00:17:23,458 --> 00:17:25,541
One William Glasdale, that is.

374
00:17:25,625 --> 00:17:27,708
Before you perish,
I think you should know the name

375
00:17:27,791 --> 00:17:29,416
of the man who's responsible.

376
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:32,000
You witch. Ulysses.

377
00:17:32,083 --> 00:17:34,166
Enemy of all mankind.

378
00:17:34,250 --> 00:17:35,625
You couldn't be killed.

379
00:17:35,708 --> 00:17:37,250
And so, I've come
to help my fellows

380
00:17:37,333 --> 00:17:39,125
reduce you to dust and ashes.

381
00:17:39,208 --> 00:17:40,875
-Here they are.
-[BATARD shrieks]

382
00:17:40,958 --> 00:17:42,125
That's right.

383
00:17:42,208 --> 00:17:43,916
When the battle drags
on like this,

384
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:47,458
the commanding officer will come
fight on the front line.

385
00:17:47,541 --> 00:17:49,125
Where's Jeanne?

386
00:17:49,208 --> 00:17:50,666
Run for cover, men!

387
00:17:50,750 --> 00:17:51,916
Go! Now!

388
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,916
Retreat!

389
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:55,291
Go!

390
00:17:55,375 --> 00:17:57,208
Hurry!

391
00:17:58,500 --> 00:17:59,916
Now! Attack!

392
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,500
♪

393
00:18:09,541 --> 00:18:10,500
What?

394
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,708
[JEANNE]
You're mine!

395
00:18:14,791 --> 00:18:16,250
[JEANNE yelling]

396
00:18:18,416 --> 00:18:19,416
[grunts]

397
00:18:20,750 --> 00:18:22,083
Jeanne! She's hit!

398
00:18:27,333 --> 00:18:29,041
♪

399
00:18:29,125 --> 00:18:30,666
[ULYSSES NOIRE]
The power granted to you

400
00:18:30,750 --> 00:18:33,666
by your Philosopher's Stone
is known as "acceleration."

401
00:18:36,250 --> 00:18:38,166
But it's not possible
to accelerate

402
00:18:38,250 --> 00:18:39,791
while you're in free fall.

403
00:18:39,875 --> 00:18:41,125
Sorry, that's the rule.

404
00:18:41,208 --> 00:18:44,083
Glasdale's attack
was only a diversion.

405
00:18:44,166 --> 00:18:45,875
Designed to make you
launch into the air

406
00:18:45,958 --> 00:18:47,625
and initiate a free fall attack,

407
00:18:47,708 --> 00:18:49,916
so that I could step in
and capture you.

408
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,541
[GLASDALE]
Poor little French girl.

409
00:18:51,625 --> 00:18:53,541
My first projectile was a feint.

410
00:18:54,541 --> 00:18:56,750
Now, have a taste
of my actual weapon.

411
00:18:58,250 --> 00:19:00,208
Ashes to ashes, demon.

412
00:19:01,416 --> 00:19:03,416
No! It can't be.

413
00:19:04,583 --> 00:19:05,666
[JEANNE]
Let go of me!

414
00:19:07,750 --> 00:19:09,833
[ULYSSES NOIRE] How fitting,
that this is the end

415
00:19:09,916 --> 00:19:11,375
God chose for us.

416
00:19:11,458 --> 00:19:14,916
We will die together,
with our purity intact.

417
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:18,625
While our dear Montmorency
watches helplessly from afar.

418
00:19:18,708 --> 00:19:21,208
[gasps]
You speak as if you know me.

419
00:19:21,291 --> 00:19:23,416
[ULYSSES NOIRE]
Ashes to ashes.

420
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:26,500
Those who pass away are destined
for the realm of the dead.

421
00:19:26,583 --> 00:19:29,375
So die, Jeanne, and we
will meet again there.

422
00:19:29,458 --> 00:19:31,708
♪

423
00:19:36,458 --> 00:19:38,125
[BOTH groan sharply]

424
00:19:38,208 --> 00:19:39,708
[gasps]

425
00:19:39,791 --> 00:19:41,833
[thumping]

426
00:19:45,833 --> 00:19:47,958
[GLASDALE] Just as
one would expect of monsters,

427
00:19:48,041 --> 00:19:50,958
you're still alive,
animated by the devil.

428
00:19:51,041 --> 00:19:53,166
But, alas, this arrow
was fashioned

429
00:19:53,250 --> 00:19:55,625
from a sliver
of the Holy Lance of Antioch.

430
00:19:55,708 --> 00:19:57,458
The spear that killed Jesus.

431
00:19:57,541 --> 00:19:59,958
It is a Philosopher's Stone.

432
00:20:00,041 --> 00:20:04,208
Even without drinking the elixir
or sacrificing my own humanity,

433
00:20:04,291 --> 00:20:06,875
I have the power to wield it
as a weapon.

434
00:20:06,958 --> 00:20:08,958
One that is capable
of killing any Ulysses,

435
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:11,083
no matter how powerful.

436
00:20:11,166 --> 00:20:13,958
Ordinarily, Ulysses can
regenerate any part of the body

437
00:20:14,041 --> 00:20:15,500
except for the brain.

438
00:20:15,583 --> 00:20:19,416
However, organs taken
by this weapon will not heal.

439
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:22,375
He who wields the Holy Lance
is an agent of God,

440
00:20:22,458 --> 00:20:24,208
sent to hunt you down.

441
00:20:24,291 --> 00:20:26,791
You're a scourge
and must be exterminated.

442
00:20:26,875 --> 00:20:28,625
Hear my holy title.

443
00:20:28,708 --> 00:20:30,708
I am the Ulysses Hunter.

444
00:20:30,791 --> 00:20:32,416
[ULYSSES NOIRE scoffs]

445
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:33,708
[ULYSSES NOIRE]
Eternal separation

446
00:20:33,791 --> 00:20:35,166
from the one you cherish.

447
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:37,541
Your love for Montmorency
is a weakness,

448
00:20:37,625 --> 00:20:39,666
for it makes you fear death.

449
00:20:39,750 --> 00:20:41,041
And then there's me.

450
00:20:41,125 --> 00:20:42,666
I'm simply awaiting death

451
00:20:42,750 --> 00:20:45,500
with nothing binding
my heart to this realm.

452
00:20:45,583 --> 00:20:48,166
I was no match for you
from the beginning.

453
00:20:48,250 --> 00:20:49,750
Montmorency.

454
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:51,708
[MONTMORENCY]
Jeanne.

455
00:20:51,791 --> 00:20:53,916
[gasps]
Please, no.

456
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:55,208
[heart thumping]

457
00:20:55,291 --> 00:20:56,791
[JEANNE]
Montmorency.

458
00:20:57,916 --> 00:20:59,166
Montmorency.

459
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:01,666
Montmorency.

460
00:21:01,750 --> 00:21:04,000
[MONTMORENCY screaming]
You can't die!

461
00:21:04,083 --> 00:21:06,500
♪

462
00:21:17,833 --> 00:21:20,083
[gasping]

463
00:21:20,166 --> 00:21:22,500
Retrieve the witch's body, now.

464
00:21:22,583 --> 00:21:24,000
And remove
the Philosopher's Stone

465
00:21:24,083 --> 00:21:25,208
from within her corpse.

466
00:21:25,291 --> 00:21:27,083
He who takes the stone from her

467
00:21:27,166 --> 00:21:30,083
will be handsomely rewarded
by the Duke of Bedford.

468
00:21:30,166 --> 00:21:31,833
[SOLDIER] Who's this man
who killed our saint?

469
00:21:31,916 --> 00:21:34,333
How are we going to win
without her?

470
00:21:34,416 --> 00:21:35,958
[clamoring]

471
00:21:36,041 --> 00:21:37,125
[MAN]
Get out of the way!

472
00:21:42,750 --> 00:21:44,583
Montmorency, we must retreat.

473
00:21:44,666 --> 00:21:46,583
Did you not hear him?
Get going!

474
00:21:46,666 --> 00:21:48,833
Snap out of it.
Do you wanna die here?

475
00:21:48,916 --> 00:21:52,000
♪

476
00:21:52,083 --> 00:21:53,416
[MONTMORENCY]
Jeanne.

477
00:21:54,458 --> 00:21:55,791
She's dead.

478
00:23:27,791 --> 00:23:29,500
[NARRATOR] The most
beautiful shape in all of nature

479
00:23:29,583 --> 00:23:30,583
is that of Etienne's breasts,

480
00:23:30,666 --> 00:23:32,041
which are almost
perfect spheres,

481
00:23:32,125 --> 00:23:33,791
uniform in height,
width and length.

482
00:23:33,875 --> 00:23:35,833
That's why I refer to them
as golden breasts.

483
00:23:35,916 --> 00:23:38,291
Episode seven,
"Rain and Memory in Brittany."

484
00:23:38,375 --> 00:23:40,125
My earlier speech had naught
to do with the preview,

485
00:23:40,208 --> 00:23:41,833
but I'm sure you'll get over it.

486
00:23:43,958 --> 00:23:46,500
[MAN] Il y a vraiment des femmes
splendides en ce Monde.

